never knew why he cried

Incapable

don't bother calling 
I've changed the number and checked the locks
and tonight you'll be in the cold
I stumbled on words I didn't think existed
trying to find the perfect way to 
punctate everything you found insignificant

it's a little tiring finding yourself follow 
the same path till the road clears
and its the beginning of the same street
with new decorations, of course

little do people know how much I notice,
though I don't care enough to remember
little do people know
that life is full of missed opportunites
even in this poem you failed to read

regret was only a name
the name of every second I found myself 
wishing I had the ability to change something
that maybe I could control 
and have my desires met
have the control to change the courses of events
rather than sit back and let them vent

details were so important 
and desire came all to easy
and the work it took to get myself to the
point of conviction seemed two steps past the point of caring

I saw you walking down the street
did you even notice me
I saw your face again
you had something on your mind
I passed our lake today
nothing turned out the way we said it would

Where did the promises break
what toll did our hearts take
I'm screaming at the lake 
we used to sit by
let our life
slowly drown itself in the sweet things that weren;t our own
I kissed you soft and gentle
but the words came to quick
goodbye

I was screaming our song 
when I blew passed the sign
a little reminder that says I'm still alive
your house is perfect in my mirror 
as I keep on driving by
and thats the way I'll remember when I let you say goodbye

simple time taken out of everything I wanted
for a smile or nod I still haven't gotten
baby steps took me away from you
one look took me back
you turned your gone 
left me only with your back
and thats not enough for me

Well the last couple days have sucked. Lora broke up with me on Sunday, I didn't know what to say, my voice kind of left me.....I think thats kind of funny, I have many tears (what a queer) on the thought of me and lora breaking up, but now it happened and I don't feel anything, well I do, but the feelings I do have make me hate myself for being so selfish....Yeah. On a funnier note Nathan and I lost our girlfriends within 24 hours of each other, made my day. I'm serious (no lora is}:) damn you:)) I was  laughing my ass off in choir when he sat down beside me. He says that he's not going to try for her again, that that was the last time that they would probebly be even friends. That sucks. I hope that won't happen to me. Right now I'm just taking each minute at a time. All my classes seem longer, the whole day seems longer, but I don't want to screw the first impression up, because maybe thats the only thing going for me right now. 

DAMN IT

I hate this, starting over like you never said any words, or held each others hand, or kissed each other goodbye, or told the other I love you before you say goodnight.  Lora wanted to tell me something, but she didn't, you know, well after bugging her for a bit, she still didn't want to talk about it so I told her I love her and that I would talk to her later....and then she asked me if I knew what she wanted to say, well, when that scene happens in sequencial order it makes it pretty obvious....so we broke up then three o'clock sunday....little did I know that nathan and danielle were going to also in the next 20 hours. It's kind of funny, Nathan has also been the one who loved the girl and went from one to the other, I always assumed that he had I don't know....but anyways he told me that he wished he could have loved someone as much as I love Lora. 

I saw this coming actually believe it or not. I think if you could call a break up and get points for the accuracy I think I did quite well. 
MY PREDICTION:

Over the phone, weekday,  before two month, I was older, she wasn't ready, and she wanted to try other people.

RESULTS:

Phone: two points (pretty obvious)
Weekday: 0 (I think that deserved five points) 
Two month: 0
Older: three points
wasn't ready: three points
other people: five points

TOTAL:13 points yeah go me

I knew she was going to break up with me on the second day of school, after she didn't want to hold my hand, or kiss me or anything in public, thats how I guessed other people. I thought she'd break up with me on a Tuesday, I don't have any particular reason, other than weekends seemed to flow better. Older, just another reason, wasn't ready, I guess I was she wasn't, that simple.
God I'm an asshole
I'm just typing, trying not to feel like shit and I think that I'm just making things worse. I'm sorry but I really need to write what I was thinking, like I said, I needed to apologise in advance for me doing anything stupid, this constitutes. That is, only if you read this. 



So I picked up my check from work and went to the bank before it closed at five. I thought I'd go to loras house, because I hate it when we act like nothings wrong. But I go over there and I park behind a raised black camaro. See I figured that she would decide and go out with either Jacob or Micah, I prepared myself to see one of them holding her hand everywhere and kissing each other goodbye, before the end of the week. It was kind of a sucker punch to see allens car there today. When I went inside Michelle and the two were in Loras bedroom, I was going to leave, but I saw Michelle's bag, so I knew it was the three of them, lol. I stuck around for about ten minutes and left. I kept telling myslef that it's her life and if I'm not a part of it, well, thats the way it goes. So I drove around until I decided to go to Brittany's house, and we talked, she told me that Lora went over to Allens after school because of no drivers ed, well, oh well, she's not mine the reality has to hit or your going to get your ass kicked by it later. I talked for a little bit and then went to work. I burnt my finger on the grill, felt good. I called Lora from work, no answer, so I was going to go home. But I turned on TBS and realised that I was relating every song to her. I needed Blink, CAN YOU BELIEVE IT THERE WAS NONE IN MY CAR!!! And I know Lora has at least one of their CD's, so I drove over there and saw the camaro, went down the road turned around and I went home.
